The prosecution has opened its case against Abdullahi Babalele, son-in-law of former Vice-President Atiku Abubakar, before a Federal High Court sitting in Lagos, who was accused of laundering $140,000 in the build-up to the 2019 general election. Babalele is being prosecuted by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC. Trial judge in the matter is Justice C. Aneke. Vanguard News Nigeria. Former Vice President and presidential candidate of Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Atiku Abubakar, alleged, yesterday, that the Federal Government was persecuting his family and business associates, following the last presidential poll. March 5, 2019 In "Headlines" Many days after raging furore over the arrest ofÂ Alhaji Babalele Abdullahi, who is the son-in-law to the defeated presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, Atiku Abubakar, the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission on Monday owned up picking up the man. March 4, 2019 In "News" The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) on Tuesday, re-arraigned Abdullahi Babalele, said to be son-in-law to former Vice-President Atiku Abubakar, over alleged money laundering charges. October 8, 2019 In "News"